  "description": [
    "IWU B a Malta Celebrates Arrival_Of Surrendered Italian War Vessels BOMBED STREETS SCENE OF LARGE VICTORY PARADE Three More Italian De stroyers Steam Into Valetta Bv JAMES WELLARD VALETTA Malta Sept 12 IP Malta held a victory celebration this morning at which the capi tulation of Italy and the surrender of the Italian fleet was feted I j ine paraae was ncaucu statue of Our Lady of Victoiy carried by four Maltese in white Bauds and a long procession of iitizens followed with banners and flags An American flag was carried proudly by one of the island s oldest inhabitants 76yearold Joseph Galea a duskyskinned whitehaired veteran born in Khar toum in the Egyptian Sudan Galea told me ne came to Malta 36 years ago but spent three years in the United States from 1924 to 1927 He said he worked in the Ford plant at Detroit I am proud to be carrying the Stars and Stripes on this great day he said because the Bri tish empire and the United States are now travelling handinhand Thats what Ive always wanted o see The procession wound through the narrow bombtorn streets up o the government square where the citzens waited"
